The paper discusses techniques for compressing and optimizing column-oriented indexes, which are commonly used in database systems. This topic falls under the scope of computer science research in databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses sorting and ordering techniques, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of determining the optimal column order, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
